                                  Appointed representatives / tied agents / PSD or EMD agents
                                




An appointed representative is a firm or individual that can act on behalf of another firm or individual (its 'principal') that is authorised by the PRA and/or FCA. A tied agent can act on behalf of another firm or individual (its 'principal') that is regulated in another country in the European Economic Area (EEA). Appointed representatives and tied agents promote or deal in the products of their principal rather than all products in the market.A PSD or EMD agent is a firm that can act on behalf of another firm (its 'principal') that is authorised or registered by the FCA as a payment or e-money institution.The principal is responsible for the activities of its agents. Please note that the "EEA Tied Agent" column is not currently in use. This relates to information that will be required under MiFID II from 3 January 2018.                                   .
                                  


Previously attached to:


‘Agent status’ shows whether an agent currently has an active relationship with any principal firm.






